description: OMBA Caramba cross country mountain bike race, presented by Midwest Off-Road Cyclists (MORC)
course: Race is being held at Sac River Trails in Springfield MO.  The course is a 10 mile loop of single track trail.
registration: Onsite Registration - Cash, Check or Visa/Mastercard/American Express
notes: All UFD rules will be in effect. USAC rules apply as well. Helmets must be worn at all times while on bike. Promoter reserves right to cancel/combine events and prize lists as necessary. Promoter reserves right to adjust start times as necessary.  A rain-out date will be utilized if weather or course conditions would make riding unsafe or harm the trails.
directions:
From KC: Hwy 71 south, to Hwy 7 to Clinton, then Hwy 13 south to Springfield, Trail entrance is on the West side of the Hwy about 2 miles before Springfield.
From I-44 in Springfield: Take Hwy 13 North, about 2 miles, entrance will be on the West side of Hwy about 1⁄4 mile AFTER big red flooring store.

Missouri State Championships - Timed Events
description:
2015 Missouri State Timed Track Championships
Saturday, May 30, 2015
course: Penrose Park Velodrome, Penrose Park, St. Louis, MO
notes:
Missouri State Championship Jerseys will be Presented for Pictures to top Missouri Resident (according to your USAC license) in individual events as long as minimum 5-rider field is met.  All final Missouri State Championship Jerseys will be presented at the Fall MoBRA Banquet in the Missouri State Champions' size for each category.  Team events are non-championship events, but bragging rights are definitely earned!  All racer categories are eligible to race as long as track certification has been completed or a previous track race at a different track has been verified; no one-day licenses will be accepted for the State Championship Events, but annual licenses will be available for purchase to those who meet racing requirements of having previously raced on the track or having finished certification. Women and Masters are allowed
to race in 4/5 or Open field in addition to the Women Open or Masters field. Elite men are not
allowed to do both fields.  Weather delays or cancellations will be posted at https://www.facebook.com/PenroseParkVelodrome.  Mixed Gender Team Sprint is 6 laps; 2 total laps must be lead by a female racer (2 consecutive by 1 female [5-rider team] or by 2 females in any order [6 rider team]); more than 2 females may comprise a team [6 rider team], but 2 laps of the team sprint is the minimum to be lead by a female.

description:
Skills instructor Jay Thomas of Roots Mountain Biking will be leading a one day skills clinic for women in the Kansas City area. The clinic will be held at Stocksdale Mountain Bike Trails in Liberty, MO on August 23rd. This clinic is ideal for beginner to intermediate skill level riders. 

Jay Thomas is an IMBA certified Level 2 instructor with *** years of experience instructing riders. If you want to brush up on biking skills and learn new ones then this is the clinic for you! Lunch will be provided as well as drinks and swag provided by Bike Stop Bicycle Store.

title: Hannah's Hope Cross & Greene Co Grand Prix
Founder's Day "Tour de Ted - Ride the Katy Trail"
2015 University of Missouri Mountain Madness
description: Mountain biking returns to Mizzou for yet another year! Be sure to come out for another awesome race weekend!
course:
The XC race returns to Cosmopolitan Park, just north of campus. The trail is a compact 4.5 mile loop with shorter but
steep uphills and downhills. While the trail is smooth and mostly nice dirt with a few rocks, the twists, turns and at times
narrow trail offers a handling challenge. Race will be run rain or shine pending officials decision.

Downhill at Mizzou returns at the same location as previous years. Course will be reworked and ready for racers and
spectators alike. Full faces required.

STXC Short track runs laps on a similar course as last year with a few new, fun trail features and a little more length.

Dual Slalom continues on a similar course to 2014 with some updates to keep it exciting for the current year.
registration:
Registration is available both online and onsite. Save yourself $5.00 per race and register online!

One day licenses will be available onsite.
notes:
